# Consult `design-md` guidance for branding work

When the task involves **branding**, **marketing UI**, **visual identity**, **design tokens**, **DESIGN.md**, or **cohesive look-and-feel** (not only default Tailwind/DaisyUI wiring):

1. Read repo-root **`DESIGN.md`** for this app’s canonical surface (scrollsmatrix jobs).
2. Read **`docs/design-md-for-agents.md`** for the generic `DESIGN.md` workflow and external catalogs.
3. Read **`patterns/goldpath/design-md-brand-ui.md`** for the checklist (copy reference `DESIGN.md`, map tokens to CSS/Tailwind).

Do not invent full palettes and type hierarchies from memory when the user expects reference-based or industry-aligned UI; follow the digest’s links and copy a `DESIGN.md` into the project when appropriate.
